# GitHub Actions CI/CD Pipeline Guidance

## Overview
Set up GitHub Actions workflows to:
1. **Build & Test** (CI): Validate code on pull requests
2. **Deploy to Dev** (CD): Auto-deploy to dev on main branch
3. **Deploy to Production** (CD): Manual approval for production deployment
4. **Provision Infrastructure** (IaC): Deploy/update Azure resources

## Architecture

```
Pull Request
    ↓
[Build & Test Workflow]
    ↓ (PR checks pass)
    ↓
Merge to main
    ↓
[Deploy to Dev Workflow]
    ↓ (dev deployment succeeds)
    ↓
Manual Approval (GitHub Environment)
    ↓
[Deploy to Production Workflow]
    ↓
Live at https://mcb.azurecontainerapps.io
```

## Azure Authentication Setup

### Step 1: Create Separate Managed Identity for GitHub Actions

```bash
# Create a separate resource group for pipeline identity (optional but recommended)
az group create --name mcb-pipeline --location eastus

# Create user-assigned managed identity
az identity create \
  --resource-group mcb-pipeline \
  --name mcb-github-actions-identity

# Capture the identity details
IDENTITY_CLIENT_ID=$(az identity show \
  --resource-group mcb-pipeline \
  --name mcb-github-actions-identity \
  --query clientId -o tsv)

IDENTITY_OBJECT_ID=$(az identity show \
  --resource-group mcb-pipeline \
  --name mcb-github-actions-identity \
  --query principalId -o tsv)

TENANT_ID=$(az account show --query tenantId -o tsv)
```

### Step 2: Set Up OIDC Federated Credentials

```bash
REPO_OWNER="YourGitHubUserOrOrg"     # Replace with your GitHub org
REPO_NAME="Mathematically_correct_builds"  # Repository name

# Create federated credential for production environment
az identity federated-credential create \
  --resource-group mcb-pipeline \
  --identity-name mcb-github-actions-identity \
  --name github-actions-prod \
  --issuer "https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com" \
  --subject "repo:${REPO_OWNER}/${REPO_NAME}:environment:production" \
  --audiences api://AzureADTokenExchange

# Create federated credential for dev environment
az identity federated-credential create \
  --resource-group mcb-pipeline \
  --identity-name mcb-github-actions-identity \
  --name github-actions-dev \
  --issuer "https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com" \
  --subject "repo:${REPO_OWNER}/${REPO_NAME}:environment:dev" \
  --audiences api://AzureADTokenExchange

# Create federated credential for staging environment
az identity federated-credential create \
  --resource-group mcb-pipeline \
  --identity-name mcb-github-actions-identity \
  --name github-actions-staging \
  --issuer "https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com" \
  --subject "repo:${REPO_OWNER}/${REPO_NAME}:environment:staging" \
  --audiences api://AzureADTokenExchange
```

### Step 3: Assign RBAC Roles

```bash
SUBSCRIPTION_ID=$(az account show --query id -o tsv)
ACR_ID="/subscriptions/${SUBSCRIPTION_ID}/resourcegroups/mcb-prod/providers/Microsoft.ContainerRegistry/registries/acrMcb..."

# Assign Contributor role on resource group (for deploying)
az role assignment create \
  --assignee ${IDENTITY_OBJECT_ID} \
  --role Contributor \
  --scope /subscriptions/${SUBSCRIPTION_ID}/resourceGroups/mcb-prod

# Assign AcrPush role on registry (for pushing images)
az role assignment create \
  --assignee ${IDENTITY_OBJECT_ID} \
  --role AcrPush \
  --scope ${ACR_ID}
```

## GitHub Configuration

### Step 1: Create GitHub Environments

```bash
# Create environments with GitHub CLI (requires GitHub CLI installed)
gh repo set-default ${REPO_OWNER}/${REPO_NAME}

# Create dev environment (auto-deploy)
gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/environments/dev -X POST

# Create staging environment (requires approval)
gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/environments/staging -X POST \
  -f 'required_reviewers[0].type=Team' \
  -f 'required_reviewers[0].reviewer[0]=mcb-reviewers'

# Create production environment (requires approval)
gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/environments/production -X POST \
  -f 'required_reviewers[0].type=Team' \
  -f 'required_reviewers[0].reviewer[0]=mcb-reviewers'
```

### Step 2: Configure Environment Variables and Secrets

Navigate to GitHub repository Settings → Environments → [Environment Name]:

**For dev, staging, and production environments:**

Environment Variables:
- `AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID`: Your Azure subscription ID
- `AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP`: mcb-prod (or your resource group)
- `AZURE_CLIENT_ID`: Client ID of the managed identity (for dev)
- `AZURE_TENANT_ID`: Your Azure tenant ID
- `REGISTRY_LOGIN_SERVER`: acrMcb....azurecr.io
- `REGISTRY_NAME`: acrMcb...
- `CONTAINER_APP_NAME`: main-app (or configured name)

### Step 3: Set Branch Protection Rules

- Require pull request reviews before merging
- Require status checks to pass (Build & Test workflow)
- Require branches to be up to date before merging

## GitHub Actions Workflow Files

### 1. Build & Test Workflow (`.github/workflows/build-test.yml`)

Triggers: Pull requests and push to main

```yaml
name: Build and Test

on:
  pull_request:
    branches: [main]
  push:
    branches: [main]

jobs:
  build-test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      
      - name: Set up Python
        uses: actions/setup-python@v4
        with:
          python-version: '3.14'
          cache: 'pip'
      
      - name: Install dependencies
        run: |
          python -m pip install --upgrade pip
          pip install -r requirements.txt
          pip install pytest pytest-cov
      
      - name: Run tests
        run: |
          pytest tests/ --cov=. --cov-report=xml
      
      - name: Upload coverage
        uses: codecov/codecov-action@v3
        with:
          files: ./coverage.xml
```

**Note**: This workflow does NOT push to ACR (no Azure login needed).

### 2. Deploy to Dev Workflow (`.github/workflows/deploy-dev.yml`)

Triggers: Push to main branch (after build-test passes)

```yaml
name: Deploy to Dev

on:
  push:
    branches: [main]
  # Prevent triggered by pull requests

jobs:
  deploy:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    environment: dev
    permissions:
      id-token: write
      contents: read
    
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      
      - name: Azure Login (OIDC)
        uses: azure/login@v2
        with:
          client-id: ${{ secrets.AZURE_CLIENT_ID }}
          tenant-id: ${{ secrets.AZURE_TENANT_ID }}
          subscription-id: ${{ secrets.AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID }}
      
      - name: Build and Push to ACR
        run: |
          az acr build \
            --registry ${{ vars.REGISTRY_NAME }} \
            --image ${{ vars.REGISTRY_LOGIN_SERVER }}/mcb-app:dev-${{ github.sha }} \
            --image ${{ vars.REGISTRY_LOGIN_SERVER }}/mcb-app:dev-latest \
            .
      
      - name: Deploy to Container Apps
        run: |
          az containerapp update \
            --resource-group ${{ vars.AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP }} \
            --name ${{ vars.CONTAINER_APP_NAME }} \
            --image ${{ vars.REGISTRY_LOGIN_SERVER }}/mcb-app:dev-latest
```

### 3. Deploy to Production Workflow (`.github/workflows/deploy-prod.yml`)

Triggers: Manual trigger (workflow_dispatch with approval)

```yaml
name: Deploy to Production

on:
  workflow_dispatch:

jobs:
  deploy:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    environment: production
    permissions:
      id-token: write
      contents: read
    
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      
      - name: Azure Login (OIDC)
        uses: azure/login@v2
        with:
          client-id: ${{ secrets.AZURE_CLIENT_ID }}
          tenant-id: ${{ secrets.AZURE_TENANT_ID }}
          subscription-id: ${{ secrets.AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID }}
      
      - name: Build and Push to ACR
        run: |
          az acr build \
            --registry ${{ vars.REGISTRY_NAME }} \
            --image ${{ vars.REGISTRY_LOGIN_SERVER }}/mcb-app:prod-${{ github.sha }} \
            --image ${{ vars.REGISTRY_LOGIN_SERVER }}/mcb-app:prod-latest \
            .
      
      - name: Deploy to Container Apps
        run: |
          az containerapp update \
            --resource-group ${{ vars.AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP }} \
            --name ${{ vars.CONTAINER_APP_NAME }} \
            --image ${{ vars.REGISTRY_LOGIN_SERVER }}/mcb-app:prod-latest
      
      - name: Health Check
        run: |
          CONTAINER_APP_URL=$(az containerapp show \
            --resource-group ${{ vars.AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP }} \
            --name ${{ vars.CONTAINER_APP_NAME }} \
            --query 'properties.configuration.ingress.fqdn' -o tsv)
          
          curl -f https://${CONTAINER_APP_URL}/health || exit 1
```

### 4. Infrastructure Provisioning Workflow (`.github/workflows/infra-deploy.yml`)

Triggers: Manual trigger (for infrastructure updates)

```yaml
name: Deploy Infrastructure

on:
  workflow_dispatch:
    inputs:
      environment:
        description: 'Environment to deploy'
        required: true
        default: 'dev'
        type: choice
        options:
          - dev
          - production

jobs:
  deploy-infra:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    environment: ${{ github.event.inputs.environment }}
    permissions:
      id-token: write
      contents: read
    
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      
      - name: Azure Login (OIDC)
        uses: azure/login@v2
        with:
          client-id: ${{ secrets.AZURE_CLIENT_ID }}
          tenant-id: ${{ secrets.AZURE_TENANT_ID }}
          subscription-id: ${{ secrets.AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID }}
      
      - name: Validate Bicep
        run: |
          az bicep build --file infra/main.bicep
      
      - name: Deploy Infrastructure
        run: |
          az deployment group create \
            --name mcb-infra-${{ github.run_id }} \
            --resource-group ${{ vars.AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP }} \
            --template-file infra/main.bicep \
            --parameters infra/main.parameters.json
```

## Setup Checklist

- [ ] Create separate managed identity for GitHub Actions
- [ ] Set up OIDC federated credentials (dev, staging, production)
- [ ] Assign RBAC roles (Contributor, AcrPush)
- [ ] Create GitHub environments (dev, staging, production)
- [ ] Configure environment variables
- [ ] Set branch protection rules
- [ ] Create workflow files in `.github/workflows/`
- [ ] Test workflows with sample pull requests
- [ ] Verify deployments in Azure Portal

## Security Best Practices

✅ **Implemented**:
- OIDC federation (no stored secrets)
- Role-based access control (least privilege)
- Environment approvals for production
- Branch protection rules
- Separate managed identity for CI/CD

## Deployment Flow

1. **Developer** pushes code to GitHub
2. **Build & Test** workflow runs (public, no auth needed)
3. If PR → merged → **Deploy to Dev** runs (auto)
4. Dev deployment succeeds → manual **Deploy to Production** button available
5. **Production** deployment requires approval (team review)
6. **Infrastructure** can be updated manually via workflow_dispatch

